text.section:
Using restricted ammunition during the commission of a crime is:
A Class D felony if no shot is fired;
A Class C felony if a shot is fired and no person is killed or wounded thereby;
A Class B felony if a shot is fired and a person other than the defendant or an accomplice of the defendant is wounded by the shot; and
A Class A felony if a shot is fired and a person other than the defendant or an accomplice of the defendant is killed by the shot.
